<br>
One thing I and the other mages in the guild do is when there are going to be lots of adds to cope with, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>/assist</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> the enchanters and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>malosini</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> everything they target with mezzes or whatever.  Malosini does not break mezz, and is very low aggro.<br>
<br>
One reason I like group damage shields is that it helps me distinguish different mobs with identical mobs.  When I target them, and I see the health bar jump a little, then I know I have targetted a different one, and I can malosini.<br>
<br>
Barring group DS, while waiting for pulls with a full mana bar, I like to DS shamans and enchanters, who are likely to get aggro.<br>
