<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Focus Items</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> These ARE important to the raid.  In my guild we don't have too many people with permanent focus level 4 items, so my summoned stuff is valuable.  I have most of them trained to ask me for the stuff right away while we are forming up, but I will ALWAYS make items for people who ask (I usually just yell at them and make sure they know to ask at the beginning next time).  The same applies for pet summons.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Mod Rods</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> I mass mod rod at the beginning of the raid and then give singles as people need them.  Nukers do not get single rods... the mana transfer isn't effective enough for that to be worthwhile.  I have all the healers and buffers trained to /tell me for rods, bcause it is VERY easy to /rt and target them, then cast.  I will also MGB rods right before a boss mob.  When you do this, it is important to tell people you are going to do this and to destroy partial mod rods. (Nothing worse than doing MBG then 30 seconds later having a cleric tell you they need a rod cause they had one charge left on an old one when you did the mass.)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>CoH</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> I am always grouped with a wizzy or druid on raids.  If we need to CoH a replacement in, someone drops from the group, the wizzy/druid pops to zin, and I coh them both back.  The whole thing takes about a minute.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Damage Shield</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> 45 point Damage Shield just plain rocks.  I ALWAYS keep DS up on the main tank.  And when the offtanks have something to play with, I toss a DS on them also.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Pets</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> I know when and where I can and can't use pets.  My guild trusts me to know this and control my pet.  They rarely say anything regarding my use (or non use) of a pet.  If in doubt though... don't use it.  The DPS a pet provides isn't worth the risk unless you are confident it is ok to use a pet in that situation.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Fighting</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> I coordinate with the shammys for debuffing.  The designated malo shammy sticks malo in... I follow with malosini... and slow hits right after that.  It's nice to be able to take part of the debuffing load and I consider it a main role of mine on raids.  After malosini is in, I nuke as much as I can and still maintain mana for debuffing, rods, and damage shields.<br>
<br>
That's how I see the role of mages on my raids.  It's a lot better than when I was constantly torpored so I could drop 12 rods per minute for the whole raid <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
