<br>
What malosini means is that:<br>
<br>
Every single caster has a *vastly* improved chance of landing any debuff or dd on the mob (save disease based stuff)<br>
<br>
The chance of a dd landing for full rather than partial damage has likewise skyrocketed.<br>
<br>
Any meleer (including pets) also has a *vastly* improved chance of any proc effect landing on the mob.<br>
<br>
For mesmerized mobs the likelihood of a resist on renewing mez has dropped enormously - which saves the mezzer mana and enhances the safety of group/raid.<br>
<br>
The extremely small amount of aggro generated by malosini also means that the mage remains quite safe while doing this. The tash line of enchanters on the other hand can and often does generate a very large amount of aggro for the enchanter. And the effect of malosini is greater than that of tash -- albeit a resistable effect. <br>
<br>
